# In-suite axum + SSE patterns for Banshee to copy

## Crate versions (from simaris-server + vauban-server)
- `axum = "0.7"` (both)
- `tokio = { version = "1", features = ["full"] }` (vauban) / `["macros","rt-multi-thread","net","signal"]` (simaris-server)
- `tokio-stream = { version = "0.1", features = ["sync"] }` (vauban)
- `tower-http = { version = "0.6", features = ["trace"] }` (simaris-server), `"0.5"` (vauban)
- `rust-embed = "8"` (simaris-server — static assets baked into binary)
- `mime_guess = "2"` (simaris-server — MIME inference for embedded assets)
- `futures = "0.3"` (vauban — stream mapping)

## SSE handler pattern (from vauban-server/routes.rs)
```rust
use axum::response::sse::{Event, KeepAlive, Sse};
use std::convert::Infallible;
use futures::stream::Stream;

pub async fn watch_canvas(State(app): State<AppState>, Query(q): Query<...>) -> Response {
    match sse_stream(app.kernel.clone(), q.path) {
        Ok(stream) => Sse::new(wrap_events(stream))
            .keep_alive(KeepAlive::default())
            .into_response(),
        Err(e) => ApiError::from(e).into_response(),
    }
}

fn wrap_events<S>(stream: S) -> impl Stream<Item = Result<Event, Infallible>>
where S: Stream<Item = WatchEvent>
{
    stream.map(|ev| {
        let json = serde_json::to_string(&ev).unwrap_or_else(|_| "{}".into());
        Ok(Event::default().data(json))
    })
}
```

## Blocking → async bridge pattern (from vauban-server/sse.rs)
```rust
// Bridge std::sync::mpsc (file-tail / blocking reader) → tokio SSE
let (tx, tok_rx) = tokio::sync::mpsc::channel::<T>(64);
tokio::task::spawn_blocking(move || {
    while let Ok(event) = rx.recv() {
        if tx.blocking_send(event).is_err() { break; }
    }
});
ReceiverStream::new(tok_rx)  // tokio_stream::wrappers::ReceiverStream
```
This pattern maps directly: file-tail lines → tx.blocking_send → SSE events.

## Static assets pattern (from simaris-server/main.rs)
```rust
#[derive(RustEmbed)]
#[folder = "../web/"]
struct WebAssets;

async fn serve_asset(Path(path): Path<String>) -> Response {
    let mime = mime_guess::from_path(&path).first_or_octet_stream();
    match WebAssets::get(&path) {
        Some(file) => Response::builder()
            .status(StatusCode::OK)
            .header(header::CONTENT_TYPE, mime.as_ref())
            .body(Body::from(file.data.into_owned()))
            .expect("build response"),
        None => (StatusCode::NOT_FOUND, "not found").into_response(),
    }
}
// Debug builds: reads from disk on each request (hot reload).
// Release builds: files embedded verbatim.
```

## Bind/serve pattern (both servers)
```rust
let listener = tokio::net::TcpListener::bind(addr).await?;
axum::serve(listener, router).await?;
```
simaris-server: `0.0.0.0:3535` (all interfaces — Tailscale reachable)
vauban-server: `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only)
→ Banshee should use `0.0.0.0` (or configurable) to be reachable over Tailscale from phone.

## Router nesting pattern (simaris-server)
```rust
let api = Router::new()
    .route("/stats", get(...))
    .nest("/api", api)
    .route("/", get(serve_index))
    .route("/*path", get(serve_asset))
    .layer(TraceLayer::new_for_http());
```

## Graceful shutdown (simaris-server)
`axum::serve(listener, app).with_graceful_shutdown(shutdown_signal()).await?`
Signal handler: `tokio::signal::ctrl_c()` + `SIGTERM` (unix only).
